Example
Return the x and y coordinates of the new window relative to the screen:

Copy
let myWindow = window.open("", "myWin"); 
myWindow.document.write("<p>This is 'myWin'"); 
myWindow.document.write("<br>ScreenLeft: " + myWindow.screenLeft); 
myWindow.document.write("<br>ScreenTop: " + myWindow.screenTop + "</p>");

Description
The screenLeft and screenTop properties returns the x and y coordinates of the window relative to the screen.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
screenLeft	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
screenTop	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
window.screenLeft 
window.screenTop
Return Value
A Number, representing the horizontal and vertical distance of the window relative to the screen, in pixels.
